article.headline: Old Dominion 74, Md.-Eastern Shore 49
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Jonathan Adams scored 13 points, Abdi Lidonde had 11 and all 11 Old Dominion players scored Saturday night in a 74-49 victory against Maryland-Eastern Shore. The Monarchs (5-4) led 31-21 at halftime and held the Hawks (1-9) to 29 percent shooting in the second half. Old Dominion also scored 25 points off 18 turnovers. The Hawks got 19 points from Ed Tyson and 10 from Marc Davis, who missed nine of 11 shots. Only three other players for Maryland-Eastern Shore scored. Ben Finney added nine points, 10 rebounds and five assists for the Monarchs.
